{
  "text": "Thyroid dysfunction can be evaluated by measuring serum TSH, T [CITATION_1] and T 3 levels, but significant changes in their levels are seen late in the disease process. Several studies have indicated that on ultrasonography, reduction in thyroid echogenicity occurs at a relatively early stage in the autoimmune thyroiditis, often before overt thyroid failure, and is a strong predictor of autoimmune process even when these disorders have not been suspected clinically.",
